fr.reflexe.viewshell.api.data.types

Interface IBinaryType

  • All Superinterfaces:
    IType

    public interface IBinaryType
extends IType
    Cell data type representing a binary data value, such as a file stored in a database, or a serialized object.

    Thread safety: implementations are required to be immutable and therefore completely thread-safe.

    Since:
    1.0
    Author:
    REFLEXE Technologies

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      ICell getFileNameCell()
      Gets the cell used to store the filename associated with the cell defined by this binary type, if the cell is defined.
      ICell getFileTypeCell()
      Gets the cell used to store the file type associated with the cell defined by this binary type, if the cell is defined.
      boolean isLargeObject()
      Indicates if the binary type is a large object ("BLOB").

    • Method Detail

      • isLargeObject

        boolean isLargeObject()
        Indicates if the binary type is a large object ("BLOB"). Large objects should preferably be accessed using data streams, to avoid performance issues and excessive memory usage.
        Returns:
        true if the binary values for the cell to which this type applies should be treated as large objects.
        Since:
        1.0
        See Also:
        IBinaryData.getValueReader(), IBinaryData.getValueWriter()

      • getFileNameCell

        ICell getFileNameCell()
        Gets the cell used to store the filename associated with the cell defined by this binary type, if the cell is defined.
        Returns:
        the cell, or null if no such cell is defined (or if the defined cell cannot be resolved).
        Since:
        1.0

      • getFileTypeCell

        ICell getFileTypeCell()
        Gets the cell used to store the file type associated with the cell defined by this binary type, if the cell is defined. The file type should be stored as a standard media type in MIME format.
        Returns:
        the cell, or null if no such cell is defined (or if the defined cell cannot be resolved).
        Since:
        1.0
